        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> The build has to be automated, there is no choice.  ONAP has a shell-script build template.  Maybe start by adding a shell script here that applies the patch and launches the docker build, then we can add a JJB configuration that runs the shell script.  Also a shell script has to go into your ci-management area. You can decide which shell script is large and which small.\n\nI added a script called \"build.sh\" that will do the git magic then do the maven build then do the docker build.  Didn't do a full test but have tested piece-meal.",
